Name: Description
COVID-19 Hospitalizations: Hospitalizations are estimations that reflect the total number of people ever admitted to a hospital for COVID-19, not currently admitted. For more information on how DOHMH estimates the number of hospitalizations to COVID-19, see their technical notes. Rates are calculated using interpolated intercensal population estimates updated in 2019 by the Department of Health, and represent the rate per 100,000 people.

Name: Source Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations:
New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, COVID-19 Data (2020). Retrieved from: https://github.com/nychealth/coronavirus-data

Data are updated weekly.

Name: Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations:
Data are cumulative and do not represent new hospitalizations per day listed. Data are cumulative and do not represent new cases per day listed. Data are being collected in real-time and are preliminary and subject to change as COVID-19 response continues. Due to delays in reporting, recent data are incomplete. 
Decreases in hospitalization data after 10/6, are due to enhanced data cleaning processes which restricts the classification of hospitalizations due to COVID-19 only if the patient was admitted within 14 days of diagnosis date.
